No. 657

(October Term, 1932).

Federal Radio Comm'n v. Nelson Brothers Bond & Mortgage Co. (Station WIBO); Federal Radio Comm'n v. North Shore Church (Station WPCC); Federal Radio Comm'n et al. v. Nelson Brothers Bond & Mortgage Co. (Station WIBO); and Federal Radio Comm’n et al. v. North Shore Church (Station WPCC). No. 658

(October Term, 1932).

No. 659

(October Term, 1932).

No. 660

(October Term, 1932).

May 28, 1934.

Motions for leave to file petition for rehearing out of time; for leave to file cross petition for writs of certiorari; for leave to appoint and refer causes to special master; for rule on Federal Radio Commission to show cause why it took appeals; to vacate mandates prematurely issued; for temporary injunction restraining Johnson-Kennedy Corporation (Station WJKS) from using 560 KC; and for rule on Clerk of this Court *614to show cause why he refuses to enter appearance of August Swarz in these cases, submitted by Mr. August Swarz, and motions denied. See 289 U.S. 266.
